<paragraph id="8BE9D268FFC0FFC4D9EDBF7AFD62EFCE" blockId="1.[136,1452,1600,1801]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName id="4C56A9EBFFC0FFC4D9EDBF7AFE32EF06" box="[136,387,1600,1621]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lychnophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="osanyiniana">
<emphasis id="B9220E7AFFC0FFC4D9EDBF7AFE32EF06" box="[136,387,1600,1621]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Lychnophora osanyiniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the following combination of characters: arborescent habit, glomerulate capitulescence with subinvolucral bracts surrounding sessile heads, giving the appearance of a single head, and uniseriate pappus. These characters together set it apart from the other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
