<subSubSection id="C34C81E3FFC0FFC6D9EDBE02FDBFE88A" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE9D268FFC0FFC6D9EDBE02FDBFE88A" blockId="1.[136,1452,1848,2091]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1451,158,473]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B9220E7AFFC0FFC4D9EDBE02FEADEE01" bold="true" box="[136,284,1848,1874]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Description:</emphasis>
—Treelet, ca. 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC0FFC4D8DEBE02FE4BEE00" box="[443,506,1848,1875]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" unit="m" value="1.3">1.3 m</quantity>
tall, erect, habit ericoid, stem highly branched, branches 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC0FFC4DD1FBE02FAA3EE00" box="[1146,1298,1848,1875]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" unit="cm" value="0.265" valueMax="0.28" valueMin="0.25">0.25–0.28 cm</quantity>
diam., terete, thin, striate, pannose-tomentose, white to greyish, leaf scar 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC0FFC4DA56BE66FC0DEE24" box="[819,956,1884,1911]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.7">1.7–1.8 mm</quantity>
diam., very shallowly obtriangular. Leaves spirally alternate, simple, imbricate, ericoid, ascending, caducous, sessile, blade 2.1–5 × 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC0FFC4DDFCBEBAFAACEEC8" box="[1177,1309,1920,1947]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" unit="cm" value="0.15" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.2 cm</quantity>
, coriaceous, discolor, linear, apex acute, margin revolute, base truncate, adaxial surface glandular, green, abaxial surface tomentose, whitish, densely covered with 3–5-armed trichomes, glandular trichomes in cavities, brochidodromous, midvein prominent abaxially, alate. Capitulescence corymbiform, with 13–15 terminal glomerules similar to a single head, with subinvolucral bract in four series, 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC0FFC4DB62B12AFD39E178" box="[519,648,2064,2091]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.25" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="0.925" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.85">0.85–1 mm</quantity>
long, leafy, lanceolate to ovate-lanceolate, apex acute, white tomentose in both surfaces. Capitula homogamous, discoid, sessile; involucre slightly campanulate, 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC2FFC6DD19B9A4FB42E9EA" box="[1148,1267,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.725" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="0.45" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" unit="cm" value="2.725" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="0.45">0.45–5 cm</quantity>
long; phyllaries 8–12, 2–3-seriate; outer phyllaries 7.8–8 × 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC2FFC6DB18B9F8FD6EE98E" box="[637,735,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
, lanceolate-elliptic, incanous, sparsely glandular, bronze, apex acuminate, margin slightly serrulate, inner phyllaries 6.5–8 × 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC2FFC6DA21B9DCFC7FE852" box="[836,974,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.5 mm</quantity>
, lanceolate to linear-lanceolate, glandular, bronze, apex caudate, margin serrulate. Florets 3 per head, hermaphrodite, fertile; corolla actinomorphic, violet, tube 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC2FFC6D9EDB814FF4AE81A" box="[136,251,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="4.35" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="4.0">4–4.7 mm</quantity>
long, cylindrical, glandular, lobes 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC2FFC6DBE7B814FD45E81A" box="[642,756,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5–4 mm</quantity>
long, oblong-lanceolate, glandular, apex apiculate, glandular; anther 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC2FFC6D9B1B868FEEBE83E" box="[212,346,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="2.6" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.7 mm</quantity>
long, apical appendages acute, basal appendages sagittate; style 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC2FFC6DD41B868FB1BE83E" box="[1060,1194,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="8.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="8.5">8.5–9.5 mm</quantity>
long, dark purple, with hairs below the bifurcation point of the style arms; stylopodium cylindrical, brown. Cypselae cylindrical to prismatic, 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC2FFC6D9EDB8A0FEB8E8E6" box="[136,265,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" unit="cm" value="2.05" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="1.9">1.9–2.2 cm</quantity>
long, angled, glabrous; carpopodium annular; pappus uniseriate, 
<quantity id="4CAE7F8DFFC2FFC6DD64B8A0FB3DE8E6" box="[1025,1164,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="1.7999999999999998" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.7">1.7–1.9 mm</quantity>
long, bristle paleaceous, slightly twisted, deciduous, cream.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
